# wargame_rl

RL project training DQN agents on discrete-grid tabletop wargames. Agents control multiple models (units) to capture objectives.

**Stack**: Python 3.12+ · UV · Gymnasium 1.x · PyTorch + Lightning · Wandb · Pydantic + pydantic-yaml · Typer · Loguru · Pygame
**Tooling**: Just · Ruff (fmt/lint, 88 cols) · Mypy (strict) · isort · autoflake · Pytest · Pre-commit

## Layout

- `wargame_rl/wargame/envs/` — env, reward, rendering, types
- `wargame_rl/wargame/model/dqn/` — DQN networks, Lightning module, training
- `wargame_rl/wargame/types.py` — `Experience` / `ExperienceBatch`
- `examples/env_config/` — YAML env configs
- `tests/` — Pytest suite, fixtures in `conftest.py`
- `docs/` — design docs
- `train.py` / `simulate.py` / `main.py` — entry points
